---
// Problem Section - Describes current specification pain points
---

<section data-test="problem-section" class="problem" id="problem">
  <div class="problem-container">
    <h2 class="problem-title">The Specification Problem</h2>

    <p class="problem-intro">
      Most product specifications fail because they're disconnected from implementation reality.
    </p>

    <div class="problem-grid">
      <div class="problem-item">
        <h3 class="problem-item-title">Spec Drift</h3>
        <p class="problem-item-description">
          <strong>spec drift</strong> happens when documentation becomes outdated the moment development begins. Features evolve, requirements change, and specs become historical artifacts instead of living guides.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-item">
        <h3 class="problem-item-title">Philosophy-Implementation Gap</h3>
        <p class="problem-item-description">
          There's a massive <strong>philosophy-implementation gap</strong> between what product teams envision and what engineering teams build. Intent gets lost in translation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-item">
        <h3 class="problem-item-title">Documentation Debt</h3>
        <p class="problem-item-description">
          <strong>Google Docs specs nobody reads</strong> pile up while teams rely on Slack messages and verbal context that disappears when people leave.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="problem-conclusion">
      <p>RootSpec solves this by creating <em>living specifications</em> that evolve with your code and enforce the connection between philosophy and implementation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.problem {
  padding: var(--space-64) 0;
  background: var(--color-background);
}

.problem-container {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 var(--space-16);
}

.problem-title {
  font-size: var(--text-3xl);
  font-weight: 700;
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  color: var(--color-text);
}

.problem-intro {
  font-size: var(--text-lg);
  text-align: center;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-48);
  max-width: 600px;
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}

.problem-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: var(--space-32);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-48);
}

.problem-item {
  padding: var(--space-24);
  background: var(--color-surface-elevated);
  border-radius: 12px;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.problem-item-title {
  font-size: var(--text-lg);
  font-weight: 600;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  color: var(--color-text);
}

.problem-item-description {
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin: 0;
}

.problem-conclusion {
  text-align: center;
  padding: var(--space-32);
  background: var(--color-surface-elevated);
  border-radius: 12px;
  border: 2px solid var(--color-primary-subtle);
}

.problem-conclusion p {
  font-size: var(--text-lg);
  color: var(--color-text);
  margin: 0;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.problem-conclusion em {
  color: var(--color-primary);
  font-style: normal;
  font-weight: 600;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .problem {
    padding: var(--space-48) 0;
  }

  .problem-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-24);
  }

  .problem-item {
    padding: var(--space-20);
  }

  .problem-conclusion {
    padding: var(--space-24);
  }

  .problem-conclusion p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
  }
}
</style>